  <other_name type="common_name">Western heath or white prairie aster</other_name>
  <discussion>Varieties 2 (2 in the flora):</discussion>
  <discussion>Symphyotrichum falcatum is introduced in Ontario and Illinois. It may closely resemble S. ericoides, which has smaller heads with fewer florets in denser arrays. The two can be difficult to distinguish on the Great Plains. A. G. Jones (1978) recognized two subspecies of S. falcatum, one with two varieties. Those two subspecies are treated as varieties here.</discussion>
